The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
		 Tuesday, May 11, 2004  Star Spot
 Radhika Basu Thakur Radhika Basu Thakur 																									Is this 19-year-old, with several laurels under her belt. Radhika has had two poems published on the website www.potesindia. com. The member of the Literary Society of Loreto College has also had an article published in the annual college magazine, Expressions. That, apart from participation and certificates in and outside school for creative writing.																									She hopes to ride some day. And the Aquarian is on the right track, presently pursuing a distance learning course in journalism and news writing from the London School of Journalism. Certificates of high achievement in English, a passion for penning long letters and a love for writing, she hopes, will help her achieve her goals. 																									From a young age is the former Loreto House student. Vice-captaincy of her house in Class X and XII, school awards for responsibility and cooperation, certificates for social service as part of the Leadership Training Service and for raising funds for the Cancer Centre Welfare Home and Research Institute  the list is long and impressive.																									Is another task the former tennis player  a bad back forced her off court  takes seriously. Apart from fundraising, the girl from Earle Street helped organise MentAid in school, a day dedicated to helping physically-disabled children have fun. She also participated in We Care, a two-day event in school to entertain people from old age homes in the city.																									Is the tall and slim first-year English literature student. Although she tends to avoid centrestage, Radhika co-scripted the play Blinded by Light for the annual inter-school drama festival organised by the British Council in 2002. The college drama society member worked backstage for the annual production.																									Is Radhika, with occasional appearances on the dance and theatre stage for inter-school and college fests. Not to forget her first-division marks in the examinations held by Pracheen Kala Kendra, Chandigarh, for Odissi dancing.
